startLDAPServer

public boolean startLDAPServer(String[] parameters)
starts the LDAPServer as an instance of LDAPServer.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] argument is the LDAPServer port,
parameters[2] is the LDAPServer root directory,
parameters[3] argument is the LDAPServer timeout.
If only parameters[0] is submitted the parameters will be taken from the configuration xml document in XTTProperties.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
LDAPServer, XTTProperties

stopLDAPServer

public boolean stopLDAPServer(String[] parameters)
stops all/one LDAPServers and all it's threads.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name, no additional parameters are requeired, the optional parameters[1] argument is the LDAPServer port of the LDAPServer to stop, if omitted all running servers are stopped.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
LDAPServer.closeSocket(String), LDAPServer.closeSockets()
